The paper deals with optimization problems related to wireless sensor networks (WSNs), which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and computational complexity analysis, which are relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of Markov approximation framework, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
